                        <p class="text-white-75 mb-4">People in Scotland have been dancing traditional dances for hundreds of years.
In 1923 the Scottish Country Dance Society started to collect these dances and write them down. The society ( now the Royal Scottish Country Dance Society) has now published more than 50 books of dances and there are over 20,000 dances available online.
Some of the most popular dances like the Dashing White Sergeant and Strip the Willow are often danced at weddings, parties and ceilidhs.
Dances can be described in words or by using diagrams.
This project will help you learn about and dance some traditional dances.</p>
